˙˙      Introduction
˙       ------------
            This text file contains information to hopefully  solve  any
        problems you may encounter when playing Evasive Maneuvers.
        
            Your first course of action should be to swear loudly.    If
        you have a cluttered computer desk, you should then take an  arm
        and wipe the desk clean with one quick back-hand motion.
        
            Now you've let off sufficient steam...
        
        
˙˙      Error Messages
˙       --------------
˙       
            Evasive Maneuvers generates  the  following  error  messages
        when an error occurs.  Following each message  is  the  solution
        to the problem.
        
˙       "This program requires at least a 386."
˙       
            Evasive Maneuvers requires at least a 386 processor  to  run
        and it doesn't detect one.
        
˙       "Evasive Maneuvers requires VGA"
˙       
            Evasuve Maneuvers requires VGA to run and it doesn't  detect
        one.
        
˙       "Run SETUP.EXE to configure Evasive Maneuvers for your System"
˙       
            Evasive  Maneuvers  hasn't  been  setup  for  your   system.
        Normally, Evasive Maneuvers  will  run  the  SetUp  program  for
        you, if it can't do that it displays this message.  The solution
        is to run SETUP.EXE yourself then run EVASIVE.EXE again.
        
˙       "Evasive Maneuvers requires <some number> bytes of free memory
˙       with this SetUp!"
˙       
            Evasive Maneuvers checks how much free  conventional  memory
        (below 640K) you have when it first runs.   If  you  don't  have
        enough Evasive Maneuvers aborts with this message.  The solution
        is to free up more memory or  lower  Evasive  Maneuvers'  memory
        requirements, for example, turn sound and/or music off.
        
˙       "<Somewhere>: Resource File Error!"
˙       
            A resource file is missing or there  is  a  problem  reading
        it.  Re-install the game.    If  that  doesn't  help,  it  maybe
        necessary to obtain another copy from a different source.
        
˙       "<Somewhere>: Resource Error!"
˙       
            Evasive Maneuvers was unable to load  a  file  it  requires.
        Most likely the game requires even more memory then  it  checked
        for at the beginning.  The solution is to free  up  more  memory
        or lower Evasive Maneuvers' memory  requirements,  for  example,
        turn sound and/or music off.
            It's also possible the resource is bad, in  which  case  you
        may try re-installing the game.  If that doesn't help, it  maybe
        necessary to obtain another copy from a different source.
        
˙       "Installing <some device> driver"
˙       
            Evasive Maneuvers is  having  a  problem  loading  a  driver
        you've specified in SETUP.EXE.    Try  rebooting  to  reset  the
        device.  A previous program using the device may  have  left  it
        in an  unstable  state.    If  there  are  still  problems,  run
        SETUP.EXE and pick another device from the same group.
        
        
˙˙      Computer Lock-Ups
˙       -----------------
˙       
            For unknown problems such  as  a  computer  hanging,  things
        become  more  difficult  to  solve.    Obscure  software  and/or
        hardware conflicts can  occur  because  everyone's  computer  is
        different.  Here are some suggestions:
        
            - Change your sound effect selection to No Sound.
            - Change your music selection to No Music.
            - Re-install the game in a new directory
            - Reboot with as little as necessary running.  Try a clean
              boot disk.
        
            I've heard of random hangs when using the  PC  Speaker  with
        QEMM in Stealth mode.  Disabling QEMM allowed the PC Speaker  to
        work flawlessly.  Also selecting No Sound for the sound  effects
        selection allowed the game to play under Stealth mode.
        
        
˙˙      Still Having Problems?
˙       ----------------------
˙       
            When all else fails, perhaps a friend, someone on a network,
        or a co-worker may be able to solve your problem.  You may  also
        write to us, the address is in the order form,  however  it's  a
        slow process and not very interactive.  Please include  detailed
        information about  your  problem  and  your  computer,  such  as
        print-outs of AUTOEXEC.BAT and CONFIG.SYS.  We probably won't be
        able to help out with hangs, but as more people write we'll  see
        common  components  among  the  computers  and  maybe  able   to
        identify the problem.
        
